article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 75, Cent. Arkansas 63
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Jordan Glynn scored 21 points and finished with 15 rebounds as Stephen F. Austin defeated Central Arkansas 75-63 Wednesday night. Glynn was 7 of 9 from the field and helped the Lumberjacks (10-4, 1-1 Southland) outrebound the Bears 43-23. Dewan Clayborn and Mike Pouncy each scored 14 points to lead Central Arkansas (4-11, 0-2), which lost its third straight. Stephen F. Austin led by seven at halftime before the Bears pulled to within 38-37 with 16:34 remaining. The Lumberjacks then put together a 16-0 run and led by at least 10 the rest of the way. Stephen F. Austin scored the game's first eight points and went into intermission up 36-29. Jereal Scott added 10 points for the Lumberjacks.
